\newlabel{multi-introductory-example-slices}{{2.1.1}{86}{Here are three vertical slices of the graph of the function $f(x,y) = x^2 + y^2$. From left to right, they are the $x = 0, x = 1$, and $x = 2$ slices, respectively}{figure.357}{}}
